rter\nwavelengths. Examining a potential counterpart of the 105mum band in the\nspectra of HD 142527 and HD 100546, we find that the broad band in the spectra\nof these young stars - extending from 85 to 125 mum - cannot be due to\nmontmorillonite or any of the hydrous silicates we studied, since these\nmaterials have sharper bands in the FIR wavelength range than previously\nassumed, especially at low temperatures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Oct 2008 09:50:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
