 hosted fully coherent\nfields at z~1. After a major merger, the strength of the turbulent field is\nenhanced by a factor of a few. Conclusions. This evolutionary scenario can be\ntested by measurements of polarized synchrotron emission and Faraday rotation\nwith the planned SKA. We predict an anticorrelation between galaxy size and\nratio between ordering scale and galaxy size (abridged).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 17 Oct 2008 10:10:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 18 Nov 2008 12:57:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
